{"builtWith":"0.15.15","comments":[{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":"                                          // hydrogen // gpu // compute-kernel"},{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":" | ComputeKernel — GPU Compute Abstractions for Effect Processing"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Design Philosophy"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Hyper-responsive effects require GPU compute for:"},{"LineComment":" | - Real-time blur (Gaussian, radial, directional)"},{"LineComment":" | - Glow with bloom and color cycling"},{"LineComment":" | - Particle physics simulation"},{"LineComment":" | - Noise generation (Perlin, Simplex, FBM)"},{"LineComment":" | - Diffusion model inference (latent space fills)"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | This module defines **pure data** representing compute operations."},{"LineComment":" | The interpreter converts these to WebGPU compute shaders."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Tensor-Native Model"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Every compute kernel operates on tensors:"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ```"},{"LineComment":" | ComputeKernel :: InputTensors -> OutputTensor"},{"LineComment":" | ```"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Where tensors have shape `[N, C, H, W]` (batch, channels, height, width)."},{"LineComment":" | This matches both GPU memory layout and ML model expectations."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## At Billion-Agent Scale"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Kernels are deterministic data:"},{"LineComment":" | - Same kernel + same input = same output (always)"},{"LineComment":" | - Kernels can be serialized, hashed, cached"},{"LineComment":" | - Multiple agents can share kernel definitions"},{"LineComment":" | - GPU batches kernels across agents efficiently"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## WebGPU Mapping"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Each kernel variant maps to a compute shader:"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | | Kernel   | Workgroup | Dispatch        |"},{"LineComment":" | |----------|-----------|-----------------|"},{"LineComment":" | | Blur     | 16x16x1   | (W/16, H/16, 1) |"},{"LineComment":" | | Glow     | 16x16x1   | (W/16, H/16, 1) |"},{"LineComment":" | | Noise    | 8x8x8     | (W/8, H/8, C/8) |"},{"LineComment":" | | Particle | 256x1x1   | (N/256, 1, 1)   |"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Module Structure"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | This is the leader module that re-exports all submodules:"},{"LineComment":" | - Core: Input/output, config, conditions"},{"LineComment":" | - Types: ComputeKernel sum type"},{"LineComment":" | - Blur: Gaussian, directional, radial, box"},{"LineComment":" | - Glow: Bloom, outer, inner"},{"LineComment":" | - Noise: Perlin, simplex, FBM, Worley"},{"LineComment":" | - Particle: Physics, emit, sort"},{"LineComment":" | - Color: Grading, tone mapping, color space"},{"LineComment":" | - Distortion: Displacement, warp, ripple"},{"LineComment":" | - Composite: Blend, mask, alpha"},{"LineComment":" | - Operations: Construction, dispatch, composition, presets"}],"decls":[],"exports":[],"foreign":[],"imports":[{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[135,4],"start":[127,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","GPU","ComputeKernel","Blur"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[173,4],"start":[165,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","GPU","ComputeKernel","Color"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[201,4],"start":[184,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","GPU","ComputeKernel","Composite"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[109,4],"start":[99,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","GPU","ComputeKernel","Core"]},{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[182,4],"start":[175,1]}},"moduleName":["Hydrogen","GPU","ComputeKernel","Distortion"]},{"annotation":